                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/4456: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-15T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1923—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. My 399, December 14, 11 a.m. From commander of South China Patrol: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 14, 9 p.m. Conference of Naval officers agreed that United
                            States, England, France, Portugal and Japan be represented in landing
                            force if used. Chinese press indicates Government is starting
                            antiforeign agitation. It states enormous customs revenues needed to
                            reduce taxes and cost of living are being held by the Powers”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
